<br>
I have to disagree about the concussion Rombus.  Mages have enough damage that it is not attributed to them in agro by the pet.  In order to make a pet work, less than half the damage the pet does can not be attributed to the owner.  (ie. if the pet did not absorb at least half the agro it did, the first cast of an agro spell would put the mage above the pet, and make soloing nearly impossible)<br>
<br>
As far as IC, I don't remember this much outrage when they put IC on a proc from the staff that drops in Acrylia Caverns.  It is too bad this is one of the nicest spell affect we have.<br>
<br>
As far as our Mage friends, you are asking us to tell you how to improve your pet.  Can you tell us what the dire need of improvement is for the pet if you have others that can perform satisfactorly?  Because it is 'worthless' in my opinion is not enough.  We all have spells that have little to no value, and in fact some of those just got worse (Gravity Flux).  How will the new pet help you in an area that needs work for the magician, and is the need great?<br>
<br>
I am not against improving the pet, I am curious.  Most magicains I have met seem pretty happy with their power level lately.<br>
<br>
Gwideon<br>
