#1, mages dont get snare, nor should they get snare (the class is balanced around not having it, so this can and will screw stuff up).<br>
<br>
#2, caster ai generally is as follows- spawn, agro mob, nuke till oom (maybe 1-2 rounds of melee in between), then melee. most pets follow that basic ai, though in hte thread on the mage forums, people were mentioning that the ai seemed to be better then the norm. in any case, based on this pattern, your pet will have a high initial dps, with a much lower dps once it starts to melee, followed by a higher dps later after it gets a chance to med. if you reclaim/recast it to avoid that, youre going to have a pet that is sustained burst dps, and that is not balanced.<br>
